{
  "_comment": [
    "Dataset stratification for eval.py. A single blended accuracy number hides",
    "the only thing that matters about a document-extraction system: WHICH kinds",
    "of documents it fails on. Clean generated PDFs and heavily-degraded scans are",
    "not the same problem, and averaging them together lets a strong score on the",
    "easy half mask a weak score on the hard half.",
    "",
    "Categories:",
    "  clean_synthetic    - generated by tests/generate_sample_invoices.py, rendered",
    "                       straight to PDF with no degradation. The floor case.",
    "  degraded_synthetic - the same generator's output pushed through blur / rotation /",
    "                       noise / downscale / JPEG artifacts (INV-10xx are the mild",
    "                       v1 degradations, INV-20xx the heavy v2 batch from",
    "                       generate_hard_samples.py). Ground truth is exact, because",
    "                       we know what was printed before it was degraded.",
    "  real_photo         - real-world-style vendor templates (SuperStore exports),",
    "                       hand-verified ground truth.",
    "  web_template       - third-party invoice/receipt templates collected from the",
    "                       web, hand-verified ground truth. The widest layout variety.",
    "",
    "Files without ground truth are still listed here so the manifest stays a",
    "complete inventory of the sample directories; eval.py skips them anyway."
  ],
